title: For Sale:  I have a 22 lr German made youth rifle old but in good shape single shot
postcontent:
little history about it-------German Youth Rifle, .22 LR caliber, manufactured by Deutsche Werke, Werk Erfurt, Germany between 1919 and 1939. Single-shot, tip-up breech for loading and ejecting shell; with bolt pull for cocking and safety. Deutsche Werke logo - a stylized "D" being formed by what is referred to as a "dormant lion" with the tail forming the "belly" of the D - inside a circle on breech-block and left side of stock. The left barrel reads "CAL .22 LONG RIFLE". The right hing plate is stamped "D.R.P./Germany" for Deutsche Reichspatent (Patented in Germany). The breech block is stamped "Mod. / I under the logo mentioned above. These rifles bear a strong resemblance to other "survival" rifles used by various military forces.
Overall length is ~37"; barrel length is ~19"; good bore.
Deutsche Werke AG was originally a factory that made torpedoes and later submarines for the German Kriegsmarine; they also produced motorcycles and diesel engines. The former Royal Prussian rifle factory at Spandau was once a part of Deutsche Werke (German Works.         ----------- I'm looking for 150.00 obo

title: For Sale:  Collector Guns For Sale
postcontent:
Collector gun for sale? GIVE US A BREAK!

A S&W 637 gunsmoke ? This is a current production gun that Davidsons has for $469 plus shipping. There are 41 of them on gunbroker with an avg selling price of about $450.

A Belgium Browning 22 takedown for $1800?  These weren't used at the local fair. They usually used pump winchesters. Going price on gunbroker is about $600-$800 in excellent shape.

If you want to know the true value of a gun, look on gunbroker. Look at what they are selling for, not what they are asking. You can join gunbroker for no fee and then do an advanced search and see completed auctions to see what they actually sold for.

Before you list a gun as a " Collector Item", know what you are talking about so you won't look like a scam artist or an idiot.

title: For Sale:  22 lr single shot old ww2 era youth rifle
postcontent:
little history I found about it--------German Youth Rifle, .22 LR caliber, manufactured by Deutsche Werke, Werk Erfurt, Germany between 1919 and 1939. Single-shot, tip-up breech for loading and ejecting shell; with bolt pull for cocking and safety. Deutsche Werke logo - a stylized "D" being formed by what is referred to as a "dormant lion" with the tail forming the "belly" of the D - inside a circle on breech-block and left side of stock. The left barrel reads "CAL .22 LONG RIFLE". The right hing plate is stamped "D.R.P./Germany" for Deutsche Reichspatent (Patented in Germany). The breech block is stamped "Mod. / I under the logo mentioned above. These rifles bear a strong resemblance to other "survival" rifles used by various military forces.
Overall length is ~37"; barrel length is ~19"; good bore.
Deutsche Werke AG was originally a factory that made torpedoes and later submarines for the German Kriegsmarine; they also produced motorcycles and diesel engines. The former Royal Prussian rifle factory at Spandau was once a part of Deutsche Werke (German Works--------- this gun is in good shape for its age and shoots great I'm asking 150.00 you can reply to this or best way is to text me or call 502410914five
